  "prompt": "How can I save images in Quora?",
  "response": "Saving images directly from Quora isn't a built-in feature, but you can still save images to your device using general methods. Here's how:\n\n### **On Desktop**\n1. **Right-click the image**: Hover over the image and right-click.\n2. Select **\"Save image as\"** or a similar option (depending on your browser).\n3. Choose the location on your computer where you want to save the image and click **Save**.\n\n### **On Mobile (iOS/Android)**\n1. **Tap and hold the image**: Press and hold the image until a menu appears.\n2. Select **\"Save image\"** or **\"Download image\"** (the wording may vary depending on your device or browser).\n3. The image will save to your device's photo gallery.\n\n### **Tips**\n- **Local Storage**: Make sure you know where your device saves downloaded images (usually the \"Downloads\" folder or \"Photos\" app).\n- **Attribution**: If you plan to use the image elsewhere, check Quora\u2019s terms of service and consider crediting the original source or author.\n- **Screenshots**: If you can't save the image directly, you can take a screenshot of it instead.\n\nRemember to respect copyright and intellectual property when saving or using images from Quora or any other platform.",
